14/11/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu has set up a task force to help implement judicial reforms in Albania. 
It includes representatives of the High Council of Justice, the National Judiciary Conference and the Supreme Court. 
Moisiu met with officials of the three institutions on Monday (November 13th) to discuss the European Commission's latest evaluation report on Albania's progress in the EU integration process.
In other news Monday, the ruling coalition got the votes it needed in parliament to reject a request by the opposition to sack Parliament Speaker Jozefina Topalli. 
Critics accuse her of procedural violations. 
(Albanian News, Korrieri - 14/11/06; Albanian President website - 13/11/06)
